# MernCrest Part 04 — Communication & CRM

Continue from Parts 01–03. Do not redesign or remove modules.

## Core rule

Every communication channel must connect to **ONE centralized CRM**.

Never leave customer conversations isolated.

```text
Customer → Website | WhatsApp | Live Chat | Email | IVR | Portal
→ Communication Hub → CRM → Departments
```

## Customer 360

One Customer ID. Profile aggregates orders, invoices, domains, hosting, tickets, WhatsApp, chat, calls, meetings, documents, timeline, renewals, assigned sales/support.

## Leads

Every inquiry becomes a lead (auto via `ensureLeadFromChannel`).

Stages: NEW → ASSIGNED → QUALIFIED → MEETING → QUOTATION → NEGOTIATION → WON | LOST | ON_HOLD

Kanban drag-and-drop in Admin CRM. Lead score + follow-ups + meetings required for sales workflow.

## Channels

- WhatsApp: business assistant (EN/TA/SI) + CRM identity by phone
- Live Chat: AI + human handoff → ticket + CRM
- Email inbound → ticket + CRM
- IVR: recorded voice only (no AI voice); menus 1–9; miss → voicemail/ticket/callback/CRM

## Quality

Searchable conversations · linked to customer · no duplicate leads when email/phone known · event-driven CRM updates · integrate Notifications / Analytics / Audit.
